Show HN: Eclipse: Python-fire inspired library to simplify creating CLIs in Go
text:
I'm a Go noob (coming from Python) and was missing python-fire's simplicity when writing quick CLIs in Go, hence this project.

I know this is not idiomatic Go (with magic methods and what not), I tried to minimize the magic as much as I could while still bringing most of the features I was using in python-fire.

Any feedback is appreciated!

Ask HN: How to contact a human being at Google AdSense?
text:
I'm trying to sign up for a Google AdSense account but I get this error message that "You already have an AdSense account".

I'm 100% sure that I don't have any other account. This is my first one. I don't even recognize the email address that they claim is associated with my duplicate account.

The frustrating part is that there's no way to appeal this. Not a single email address or phone number is provided on the website.

Is there any way that I can contact a real person at Google AdSense?

Ask HN: Is it a good idea to record external APIs/microservices response times?
text:
I wonder if it will be a good idea to record the external APIs or microservices response time as part of application metrics.

I do capture the response time of my API. But while analyzing a performance or latency related issues I think it will help to know the performance of the external systems as well. This can quickly point out any issues due to a downstream system or even a DB. I understand that these systems will also have these metrics available but they don't always paint the complete picture. For instance they will not include network latencies.

But on the flip side I wonder will this mean generating a lot data and maybe as well lead to increasing latency of the current API.

I wonder if this is a practice in the industry? What are your thoughts?
